# ARC Auto-Lint Integration

> THIS: Triggers ARC validation when documentation is modified.

## When This Rule Activates

This rule is invoked when:
- Creating new .md files
- Modifying existing .md files
- Requesting documentation review

---

## Pre-Commit Validation

Before committing changes to any .md file, run:

```bash
./arc-lint.sh [path/to/file.md]
```

If the file fails validation:
1. Review the error messages
2. Fix structural issues (header, footer, size)
3. Re-run until passing

---

## Quick Fix Patterns

### Missing TL;DR

Add after the title:

```markdown
## TL;DR
- [Most important action or fact]
- [Second most important point]
- [Third most important point]
```

### Missing Summary

Add blockquote after H1:

```markdown
# Title
> One-sentence summary that can stand alone.
```

### Missing CCA Annotations

Add at section starts:

```markdown
HERE: What this section covers.
THIS: What this content does.
```

### Missing Footer

Add before end of file:

```markdown
---

## Links

LINK: Related to [Other Doc](./path.md) — why related
```

### File Too Large

Split into sub-documents:
1. Identify logical boundaries (major H2 sections)
2. Extract to separate files
3. Add cross-references with LINK:
4. Update llms.txt

---

## Integration Commands

```bash
# Single file check
./arc-lint.sh docs/file.md

# All documentation
./arc-lint.sh docs/

# Generate llms.txt
./arc-lint.sh --generate-llms

# Git pre-commit hook
#!/bin/bash
./arc-lint.sh docs/ || exit 1
```

---

## Cascade/Windsurf Integration

When Cascade modifies .md files, it should:

1. **Before writing**: Check if file exists, read TL;DR first
2. **During writing**: Maintain header structure, add CCA annotations
3. **After writing**: Run `./arc-lint.sh [file]` to validate

KEEP: These steps are load-bearing for agent comprehension.
Skipping validation risks creating unreadable documentation.

---

## Memory Integration

If using Windsurf Memories:

```
Rule: Always run arc-lint.sh after modifying documentation
Type: User-generated
Scope: Project-specific
```

This ensures every documentation change is validated.
